  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cook",
  "description": "<p>Unwine is a cozy wine bar located at IOI Central Boulevard Towers, offering a laid-back atmosphere ideal for enjoying a wide selection of <strong>wines and western fusion cuisine.</strong> You will be part of the Store Opening team where you will report directed to the Outlet Chef.</p><p>In your role as the Commis at <strong>Unwine</strong>, you will work closely with the Outlet Chef to help in the menu preparation together with the back-of-house (BOH) team:</p><ul><li>Follow the Outlet Chef's guidance on kitchen operations</li><li>Prep required ingredients and sauces</li><li>Check, monitor and ensure adequate supply at the cooking stations</li><li>Prepare specific food items and stock-up of required fresh produce for the day's usage</li><li>Adhere to strict hygiene standards and good food handling practices at all times</li><li>Responsible for stock rotation by ensuring the freshness of ingredients to be used</li><li>To practice proper inventory management through the safeguarding of stock taking and ordering of supplies</li><li>Any other skill-development or ad-hoc task as assigned</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>1 to 3 years related experience in a Food & Beverage (F&B) establishment would be good but not necessary as training and guidance will be provided</li></ul><p><em>*If you do not have prior experience or limited training, we still welcome your application if you are genuinely keen to learn, grow and develop as we have a long and positive track record of developing our entry-level Commis Chefs into established CDPs, Junior Sous Chefs and Sous Chefs</em></p><ul><li>A valid Food Hygiene Certificate registered with Singapore Food Agency (SFA)</li></ul><p><em>*If you do not have a valid food hygiene certificate, the Company will arrange the training and certification</em></p><ul><li>Able to work under pressure in a fast-paced, yet fun environment</li><li>Great communication skills with positive, interpersonal skills</li><li>A team player with a good sense of job responsibility and a keen eye for details</li><li>Honest willingness to learn and grow with the Company</li></ul>",
